import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Load and preprocess the data
df_open_3 = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Jing0712/EEG-Spectral-Band-Analysis-/refs/heads/main/Paciente3_open.csv')
df_closed_3 = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Jing0712/EEG-Spectral-Band-Analysis-/refs/heads/main/Paciente3_closed.csv')

# Select EEG channels (assuming they are the first 21 columns)
eeg_channels = df_open_3.columns[:21]

# Standardize the data
scaler = StandardScaler()
df_open_3_standardized = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(df_open_3[eeg_channels]), columns=eeg_channels)

# Compute correlation matrix and eigenvectors
corr_matrix = np.dot(df_open_3_standardized.T, df_open_3_standardized) / (len(df_open_3_standardized) - 1)
eigenvalues, eigenvectors = np.linalg.eig(corr_matrix)

# Sort eigenvalues and corresponding eigenvectors in descending order
idx = eigenvalues.argsort()[::-1]
eigenvalues = eigenvalues[idx]
eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, idx]

# Normalize eigenvalues
normalized_eigenvalues = eigenvalues / np.sum(eigenvalues)

# Projections for dimensions 1, 2, and 3
def project_onto_subspace(X, subspace_basis):
    coefficients = np.dot(X, subspace_basis)
    Y = np.dot(subspace_basis, coefficients)
    Z = X - Y
    return Y, Z

channel = 'F1'
X = df_open_3_standardized[channel].values

fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(15, 15))
fig.suptitle(f'Projections for Channel {channel}', fontsize=16)

for dim in range(1, 4):
    W = np.dot(df_open_3_standardized, eigenvectors[:, :dim])
    W = W / np.linalg.norm(W, axis=0)
    
    Y, Z = project_onto_subspace(X, W)
    
    axes[dim-1, 0].plot(X, label='X')
    axes[dim-1, 0].set_title(f'Original Signal (X)')
    
    axes[dim-1, 1].plot(Y, label='Y')
    axes[dim-1, 1].set_title(f'Projected Signal (Y) - {dim}D')
    
    axes[dim-1, 2].plot(Z, label='Z')
    axes[dim-1, 2].set_title(f'Orthogonal Complement (Z) - {dim}D')
    
    for ax in axes[dim-1]:
        ax.set_xlabel('Time')
        ax.set_ylabel('Amplitude')
        ax.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# (c) X, Y, Z in the same figure for each dimension
for dim in range(1, 4):
    W = np.dot(df_open_3_standardized, eigenvectors[:, :dim])
    W = W / np.linalg.norm(W, axis=0)
    
    Y, Z = project_onto_subspace(X, W)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(X, label='Original (X)')
    plt.plot(Y, label=f'Projected (Y) - {dim}D')
    plt.plot(Z, label=f'Orthogonal Complement (Z) - {dim}D')
    plt.title(f'Comparison of X, Y, and Z - {dim}D Projection')
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
